    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2020-April/002652.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>There have been discussions among Bitcoin developers regarding vulnerabilities and proposed changes to the state machine for lightning implementations. One issue identified involves a bidding war scenario between counterparties over HTLC value, which could result in theft. Proposed solutions include pre-signed HTLC spends and adding an "RBF-enabled" requirement to the `OP_CHECKSEQUENCEVERIFY` clause.Another issue discussed is the use of low fee-rate transactions in Bitcoin contracts, which could create potential vulnerabilities for denial-of-service attacks. Proposed solutions include monitoring the global mempool and using pre-signed HTLC spends.To deal with complexity, it is important to take a systematic approach that accounts for all relevant factors. This can involve breaking down complex systems into smaller components, using modeling and simulation techniques, and studying emergent properties.Despite the challenges posed by complexity, there are also opportunities to be found. By approaching complex problems with an open mind and a strategic mindset, it is possible to make progress even in the face of daunting challenges.</summary>
